024/**
025 * Provides metadata about the API.
026 *
027 * <p>
028 * The Info Object contains required and optional metadata about the API, including the title, version, description, 
029 * terms of service, contact information, and license. This metadata can be used by client tooling and is typically 
030 * displayed in API documentation interfaces.
031 *
032 * <h5 class='section'>OpenAPI Specification:</h5>
033 * <p>
034 * The Info Object is composed of the following fields:
035 * <ul class='spaced-list'>
036 *    <li><c>title</c> (string, REQUIRED) - The title of the API
037 *    <li><c>version</c> (string, REQUIRED) - The version of the OpenAPI document (not the API itself)
038 *    <li><c>description</c> (string) - A short description of the API (CommonMark syntax may be used)
039 *    <li><c>termsOfService</c> (string) - A URL to the Terms of Service for the API
040 *    <li><c>contact</c> ({@link Contact}) - Contact information for the exposed API
041 *    <li><c>license</c> ({@link License}) - License information for the exposed API
042 * </ul>
043 *
044 * <h5 class='section'>Example:</h5>
045 * <p class='bjava'>
046 *    <jc>// Create an Info object</jc>
047 *    Info <jv>info</jv> = <jk>new</jk> Info()
048 *       .setTitle(<js>"Pet Store API"</js>)
049 *       .setVersion(<js>"1.0.0"</js>)
050 *       .setDescription(<js>"This is a sample Pet Store Server based on the OpenAPI 3.0 specification."</js>)
051 *       .setTermsOfService(<js>"http://example.com/terms/"</js>)
052 *       .setContact(
053 *          <jk>new</jk> Contact()
054 *             .setName(<js>"API Support"</js>)
055 *             .setUrl(URI.<jsm>create</jsm>(<js>"http://www.example.com/support"</js>))
056 *             .setEmail(<js>"support@example.com"</js>)
057 *       )
058 *       .setLicense(
059 *          <jk>new</jk> License()
060 *             .setName(<js>"Apache 2.0"</js>)
061 *             .setUrl(URI.<jsm>create</jsm>(<js>"http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0.html"</js>))
062 *       );
063 * </p>
064 * <p class='bjava'>
065 *    <jc>// Serialize to JSON</jc>
066 *    String <jv>json</jv> = Json.<jsm>from</jsm>(<jv>info</jv>);
067 *
068 *    <jc>// Or just use toString() which does the same as above.</jc>
069 *    <jv>json</jv> = <jv>info</jv>.toString();
070 * </p>
071 * <p class='bcode'>
072 *    <jc>// Output</jc>
073 *    {
074 *       <js>"title"</js>: <js>"Pet Store API"</js>,
075 *       <js>"version"</js>: <js>"1.0.0"</js>,
076 *       <js>"description"</js>: <js>"This is a sample Pet Store Server based on the OpenAPI 3.0 specification."</js>,
077 *       <js>"termsOfService"</js>: <js>"http://example.com/terms/"</js>,
078 *       <js>"contact"</js>: {
079 *          <js>"name"</js>: <js>"API Support"</js>,
080 *          <js>"url"</js>: <js>"http://www.example.com/support"</js>,
081 *          <js>"email"</js>: <js>"support@example.com"</js>
082 *       },
083 *       <js>"license"</js>: {
084 *          <js>"name"</js>: <js>"Apache 2.0"</js>,
085 *          <js>"url"</js>: <js>"http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0.html"</js>
086 *       },
087 *       <js>"version"</js>: <js>"1.0.1"</js>
088 *    }
089 * </p>
090 *
091 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
092 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://spec.openapis.org/oas/v3.0.0#info-object">OpenAPI Specification &gt; Info Object</a>
093 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://swagger.io/docs/specification/api-general-info/">OpenAPI API General Info</a>
094 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauBeanOpenApi3">juneau-bean-openapi-v3</a>
095 * </ul>
096 */

312   @Override /* OpenApiElement */
313   public <T> T get(String property, Class<T> type) {
314      assertArgNotNull("property", property);
315      return switch (property) {
316         case "title" -> toType(getTitle(), type);
317         case "description" -> toType(getDescription(), type);
318         case "termsOfService" -> toType(getTermsOfService(), type);
319         case "contact" -> toType(getContact(), type);
320         case "license" -> toType(getLicense(), type);
321         case "version" -> toType(getVersion(), type);
322         default -> super.get(property, type);
323      };
324   }

326   @Override /* OpenApiElement */
327   public Info set(String property, Object value) {
328      assertArgNotNull("property", property);
329      return switch (property) {
330         case "contact" -> setContact(toType(value, Contact.class));
331         case "description" -> setDescription(Utils.s(value));
332         case "license" -> setLicense(toType(value, License.class));
333         case "termsOfService" -> setTermsOfService(Utils.s(value));
334         case "title" -> setTitle(Utils.s(value));
335         case "version" -> setVersion(Utils.s(value));
336         default -> {
337            super.set(property, value);
338            yield this;
339         }
340      };
341   }
